%I A395412 #16 May 04 2026 23:58:03
%S A395412 1,2,3,5,5,5,5,2,5,7,4,7,4,6,10,3,3,5,10,6,8,5,8,7,9,5,7,8,9,3,3,6,3,
%T A395412 7,6,10,6,5,5,13,6,8,3,6,1,6,10,8,7,7,9,8,9,7,8,2,4,6,6,6,7,7,9,8,4,
%U A395412 11,9,4,7,5,5,10,5,8,6,10,12,5,6,8,8,9,7,4
%N A395412 a(n) = number of k's that make A002110(n)/A005117(k)+A005117(k) prime, A005117(k)<prime(n).
%C A395412 Number of distinct primes of the form d + P(n)/d, where P(n) is the n-th primorial A002110(n) and d<prime(n) is a divisor of P(n) and is a squarefree number (A005117).
%C A395412 Conjecture: a(n) is never equal to 0.
%e A395412 P(1)=2; prime(1)=2, A005117(1)=1, 2/1+1=3 is prime and A005117(2)=2 is not less than prime(1)=2; so a(1)=1.
%e A395412 P(2)=6; prime(2)=3; A005117(1)=1, 6/1+1=7 is prime; A005117(2)=2, 6/2+2=5 is prime; A005117(3)=3 is not less than prime(2)=3; so a(2)=2.
%e A395412 P(3)=30; prime(3)=5; A005117(1)=1, 30/1+1=31 is prime; A005117(2)=2, 30/2+2=17 is prime; A005117(3)=3, 30/3+3=13 is prime; A005117(4)=5 is not less than prime(3)=5; so a(3)=3.
%o A395412 (PARI) a(n) = my(S=0, P=prime(n)-1, Primo=vecprod(primes(n))); for(D=1, P, if(issquarefree(D) && ispseudoprime(Primo/D+D), S++)); return(S);
%Y A395412 Cf. A002110, A005117, A182987, A295741, A394782.
%K A395412 nonn,new
%O A395412 1,2
